cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper proposes a flexible convolutional autoencoder for image classification, which is a common task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of particle swarm optimization, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting that cs.LG and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the design of an architecture discovery method, which falls under the scope of AI and ML, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an approach for optimizing the architecture of the proposed model, which can be considered as a control problem, indicating that cs.SY is also a possible sub-category.
